From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ryan Chen <rchen14b@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 5 Feb 2026 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] PCI: mediatek-gen3: Add serdes lane mux configuration for
 Airoha EN7581

The Airoha EN7581 SoC has a serdes lane multiplexer register at
chip_scu + 0x18c (NP_SCU_SERDES_WIFI_SEL) that controls how serdes
lanes are routed to PCIe ports:

  - Bits [1:0] = 0x3: Route the dedicated 2-lane PCIe PHY to
    ports 0/1, enabling Gen3 x2 link width
  - Bit  [2]   = 0x4: Route the USB3 combo PHY serdes lane to
    PCIe port 2, enabling Gen2 x1

Without configuring this register, PCIe port 0 only trains at x1
link width instead of x2, halving the available bandwidth. This
matches the OEM firmware's wifi_serdes_select() initialization.

The serdes mux configuration is controlled via optional DTS
properties:
  - airoha,chip-scu: phandle to the chip_scu syscon
  - airoha,serdes-lanes-mask: bitmask of lanes to enable

Signed-off-by: Ryan Chen <rchen14b@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/pci/controller/pcie-mediatek-gen3.c | 29 +++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 29 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-mediatek-gen3.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-mediatek-gen3.c
@@ -97,6 +97,8 @@
 #define PCIE_MSI_SET_ADDR_HI_BASE	0xc80
 #define PCIE_MSI_SET_ADDR_HI_OFFSET	0x04

+#define AIROHA_SCU_SERDES_WIFI_SEL	0x18c
+
 #define PCIE_ICMD_PM_REG		0x198
 #define PCIE_TURN_OFF_LINK		BIT(4)

@@ -958,6 +960,9 @@ static int mtk_pcie_en7581_power_up(stru
 	struct resource_entry *entry;
 	struct regmap *pbus_regmap;
 	u32 val, args[2], size;
+	struct regmap *chip_scu;
+	u32 serdes_mask;
+	u32 readback;
 	resource_size_t addr;
 	int err;

@@ -991,6 +996,30 @@ static int mtk_pcie_en7581_power_up(stru
 	size = lower_32_bits(resource_size(entry->res));
 	regmap_write(pbus_regmap, args[1], GENMASK(31, __fls(size)));

+	/*
+	 * Configure the serdes lane multiplexer to route the appropriate
+	 * PHY lanes to this PCIe port. The chip_scu register at offset
+	 * 0x18c controls which serdes lanes are assigned to PCIe vs USB.
+	 * Without this, port 0 trains at x1 instead of x2.
+	 */
+	chip_scu = syscon_regmap_lookup_by_phandle(dev->of_node,
+						   "airoha,chip-scu");
+	if (IS_ERR(chip_scu)) {
+		dev_info(dev, "no chip-scu syscon, skip serdes mux config\n");
+	} else if (of_property_read_u32(dev->of_node,
+					"airoha,serdes-lanes-mask",
+					&serdes_mask)) {
+		dev_info(dev, "no serdes-lanes-mask, skip serdes mux config\n");
+	} else {
+		regmap_read(chip_scu, AIROHA_SCU_SERDES_WIFI_SEL, &readback);
+		dev_info(dev, "serdes mux before: 0x%x, setting mask 0x%x\n",
+			 readback, serdes_mask);
+		regmap_update_bits(chip_scu, AIROHA_SCU_SERDES_WIFI_SEL,
+				   serdes_mask, serdes_mask);
+		regmap_read(chip_scu, AIROHA_SCU_SERDES_WIFI_SEL, &readback);
+		dev_info(dev, "serdes mux after: 0x%x\n", readback);
+	}
+
 	err = phy_set_mode(pcie->phy, PHY_MODE_PCIE);
 	if (err) {
 		dev_err(dev, "failed to set PHY mode\n");
